1
00:00:33,116 --> 00:00:37,828
(♪ "The Face of Love" by
Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan with Eddie Vedder)

2
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:15,365
♪ Look in the eyes of the face of love

3
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:21,497
♪ Look in her eyes, oh, there is peace

4
00:01:21,664 --> 00:01:27,336
♪ No nothin' dies within pure light

5
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:32,841
♪ Only one hour of this pure love

6
00:01:33,176 --> 00:01:38,847
♪ To last a life of 30 years

7
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:44,937
♪ Only one hour, so come and go ♪

8
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:10,129
- Hi, Sister Helen.
- Hi. How ya doin'?

9
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:24,393
Well, if it ain't the late Sister Helen.

10
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:26,520
I got a note from my mama, Idella.

11
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:30,065
Do you need a new composition book?
How about you, Melvin?

12
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:34,653
The resident counselor wants us at their
meeting tomorrow. Can you be there?

13
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:37,239
Yes. Oh... New poetry books.

14
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:40,200
- Your poem got all smudged.
- Smudged?

15
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:43,412
Sister Helen, I got
another letter from that guy.

16
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:47,374
- Which guy is that?
- Angola inmate. Death row.

17
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:48,500
Oh, yeah.

18
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:51,920
Could you write to him?
He could use some friendly words.

19
00:02:52,088 --> 00:02:54,840
Sure. I'll come up after the class.

20
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:58,427
- It got smudged.
- You can still read it.

21
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:07,269
"There's a woman
standin' there in the dark

22
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:09,730
and she's got big arms to hold you,

23
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:12,774
but you won't feel
those arms, that hug,

24
00:03:12,942 --> 00:03:15,152
till you can see her face.

25
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:20,032
So you stand there waiting
for the light at the end of the road."

26
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:25,120
- Idella, that is so fine.
- Thank you.

27
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:34,087
My lawyer seems to have disappeared.

28
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:36,131
So I could use some help
on the legal end,

29
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:39,468
but I'd take a kind word or a visit.

30
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,553
It gets real quiet here sometimes.

31
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:45,140
None of these guys on the row
can afford attorneys for appeals.

32
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:48,477
We get frantic phone calls
from death row inmates,

33
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:51,730
- begging us to find them attorneys.
- Who work for nothin'.

34
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:54,691
That's right. Each petition
takes hours to prepare.

35
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:58,070
Attorneys aren't exactly
lining up for the job.

36
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:03,283
(♪ "The Face of Love")

37
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:21,093
Dear Sister Helen,

38
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:26,723
Thank you for writin' to me. I'm writin'
from my home, my six by eight foot cell.

39
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,393
I'm in here 23 hours a day.

40
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:32,354
We don't work on death row.

41
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:33,647
We're special here.

42
00:04:33,815 --> 00:04:36,984
They keep us away from the
general population of the prison.

43
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:40,529
We're the elite, cos we gonna fry.

44
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:43,532
It's hard not to get soft in this cell.
I press my footlocker,

45
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:48,537
try to get my muscles in shape,
but it's hard not to get fat.

46
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:52,541
Rice, potatoes, pancakes, beans.

47
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:57,796
Sometimes I feel like a sow that's being
fattened up for a Christmas slaughter.

48
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:01,300
I had a dream that I was
about to be fried in the chair

49
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:04,594
and a guard came into my cell
with a chef's hat on.

50
00:05:04,762 --> 00:05:06,471
He started to roll me in breadcrumbs,

51
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:09,224
lickin' his chops and all.

52
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:13,145
Maybe I'm weird to have dreams like
that, but your mind does funny things

53
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:16,648
when you're surrounded
by people that wanna kill you.

54
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:20,235
Anyway, thanks for writin'.

55
00:05:20,403 --> 00:05:22,904
I don't get many letters or visitors.

56
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:26,950
No one in my family seems able
to make the trip out here. I understand.

57
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:30,579
It's a long drive from Slidell.

58
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:37,252
- Good morning.
- Good morning, Father.

59
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:41,006
- Sister...
- Helen Prejean. Nice to meet you.

60
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:54,978
- Have you been in a prison before?
- No, Father.

61
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:56,438
Sister Clement and I sang

62
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:59,024
at the juvenile detention center
in New Orleans.

63
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:02,152
We sang "Kumbaya"
and the boys really liked it.

64
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:08,200
They started makin' up their own verses,
singin' "Someone's escapin', my Lord..."

65
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:11,495
The guards made us
sing a different song.

66
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:14,206
Where is your habit?

67
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:17,209
Our sisters haven't worn
the habit for 20 years, Father.

68
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:21,463
You are aware of the papal request
regarding nuns' garments, aren't you?

69
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:26,885
I believe the Pope said
"distinctive clothing", not habits.

70
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:31,640
Well, I'm sure you will interpret it
in your own way. Whatever's convenient.

71
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:35,018
Matthew Poncelet.

72
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:39,606
I remember him from the news.
Him and another fella

73
00:06:39,774 --> 00:06:43,485
shot two children in the back
of the head on a lovers' lane.

74
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:47,656
Raped the girl,
stabbed her several times.

75
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:52,244
Do you know what you're gettin' into?

76
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:56,081
So what is it, Sister?

77
00:06:56,249 --> 00:07:01,420
Morbid fascination?
Bleedin'-heart sympathy?

78
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:04,756
He wrote me and asked me to come.

79
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:07,008
There's no romance here, Sister.

80
00:07:07,176 --> 00:07:10,804
No Jimmy Cagney "I'm wrongly accused.

81
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:14,474
If I only had someone to believe in me."

82
00:07:14,642 --> 00:07:20,272
They are all con men and they will take
advantage of you every way they can.

83
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:25,986
You must be very, very careful.
Do you understand?

84
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:27,320
Yes, Father.

85
00:07:27,488 --> 00:07:31,116
These men don't see many females.

86
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:35,036
For you to wear the habit
might help instill respect.

87
00:07:35,204 --> 00:07:40,250
For you to flout authority
will only encourage them to do the same.

88
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:57,309
Woman on the tier!

89
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,958
You can wait over there.
We'll bring your man out for you.

90
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,335
Well, Matthew, I made it.

91
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:10,298
Thanks for comin', ma'am.

92
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:14,344
Never thought I'd be visitin'
with no nun.

93
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:25,730
- So you're a nun.
- Yep.

94
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:36,741
I'm here to listen, and whatever
you wanna talk about, that's fine.

95
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:38,660
You're very sincere.

96
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:41,413
What do you mean?

97
00:09:42,331 --> 00:09:43,665
- You never done this before?
- No.

98
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,584
Never been this close to a murderer?

99
00:09:45,751 --> 00:09:47,752
Not that I know of.

100
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:50,005
You live in St. Thomas.
Lots of niggers.

101
00:09:50,172 --> 00:09:53,341
They knock each other off
like beer cans off a fence.

102
00:09:55,094 --> 00:09:57,804
When I got your letter
and I seen "Helen" on it,

103
00:09:57,972 --> 00:09:59,514
I thought of my first ex-old lady.

104
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:03,852
I almost ripped it up.
She turned me in. Called the cops.

105
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,605
Orphaned our kid, the stupid bitch.

106
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:08,690
- You've got a kid?
- Yeah, a con with a kid.

107
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:10,191
- Girl or boy?
- Girl.

108
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:12,277
What's her name?

109
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:14,863
- You ask a lot of questions.
- I don't know you.

110
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:16,323
Well, never mind.

111
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:24,664
In your letter you say
you work with poor people.

112
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:28,293
Your daddy was a lawyer.
You come from money, don't you?

113
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:30,378
Some.

114
00:10:30,546 --> 00:10:34,591
And you live in St. Thomas projects?
I don't know who's crazier, you or me.

115
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:37,218
- I live where I work.
- Yeah. In a slum.

116
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,804
- What about you?
- I live here.

117
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:42,223
You... were brought up poor?

118
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:46,102
Ain't nobody with money on death row.

119
00:10:46,854 --> 00:10:49,105
Then you and I have
somethin' in common.

120
00:10:49,273 --> 00:10:53,026
- What's that?
- We both live with the poor.

121
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:55,654
Mm.

122
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:07,666
Ain't you gonna ask me what I done?

123
00:11:09,085 --> 00:11:12,587
- The chaplain filled me in.
- Farley?

124
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:15,507
He's a very religious man.

125
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:27,268
I didn't kill nobody.
Carl went crazy on me.

126
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:30,271
- Carl?
- Vitello. He oughta be sittin' here.

127
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:34,734
Went nuts on me. I was scared,
did what he said, held that boy back.

128
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:36,361
He killed them.

129
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:40,573
You watched him kill these kids?

130
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:42,992
I'll tell you the truth, ma'am.

131
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:47,580
Me and Carl were loaded on downs,
acid and booze when this happened.

132
00:11:47,748 --> 00:11:51,334
I hadn't slept in two nights.
I was outta my head.

133
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:53,628
But I didn't kill 'em.

134
00:11:55,005 --> 00:11:57,549
I didn't kill nobody.
I swear to God I didn't.

135
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:02,053
Ally.

136
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:04,597
- Ally?
- Her name.

137
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:11,479
- She's cute.
- She's 11... or 12. I don't know.

138
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:15,108
She was born when I was first in prison.
I seen her once.

139
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:18,319
- When was that?
- When she was three.

140
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,489
- Do you write to her?
- I don't know where she is.

141
00:12:21,657 --> 00:12:24,576
She's in Texas somewhere.
Foster parents.

142
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:26,911
Go on and finish up, Sister.

143
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,586
Look... They're about
to go on a killin' spree here.

144
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:37,338
They're gonna zap
this guy Tobias tonight.

145
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:42,177
The guards are takin' bets on who's
next. I'm at even odds. It's not good.

146
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:45,847
So I got two chances: The pardon board
or the federal appeals court.

147
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:49,267
I wrote the motion on the appeal,
but I need somebody to file it.

148
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:50,977
Can you help me with that?

149
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:55,190
You know how to write a motion?

150
00:12:55,357 --> 00:12:58,109
When your back's against the wall,
you learn the law real fast.

151
00:12:58,277 --> 00:13:01,571
Call it special motivation.
I been on death row six years.

152
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:04,324
I've studied every law book
I can get my hands on.

153
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:08,328
This stuff is about my case -
transcripts of the trials, legal papers.

154
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,372
Maybe they'll help you
get ahold of things faster.

155
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:15,043
You rustle me up a lawyer,
we can file a motion for appeal.

156
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:23,718
- You ain't comin' back.
- No, I... Are these your only copies?

157
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:27,722
I got my own copy. But if you ain't
gonna help me, I don't wanna waste 'em.

158
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:31,017
I'll do my best.
And I appreciate your trust.

159
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:35,188
Sister, I don't trust nobody in here.

160
00:13:35,356 --> 00:13:39,150
But you don't kiss my ass or preach
that hellfire and brimstone crap.

161
00:13:39,318 --> 00:13:42,362
I respect that. You got guts.

162
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:46,241
You're livin' in a neighborhood
with every nigger carryin' a gun.

163
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:52,080
Come on, Helen. Hit it!

164
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:11,182
Playing possum, huh? You think
you can trick us, you dumb animal?

165
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:13,268
You think you can fool us?

166
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:30,785
- How fast was I goin'?
- 75 miles an hour, ma'am.

167
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:32,787
Wow!

168
00:14:32,955 --> 00:14:35,540
- Are you a nun?
- Yes, sir.

169
00:14:37,084 --> 00:14:39,544
Never gave a ticket to no nun before.

170
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:44,632
Gave a ticket to a guy from the IRS
one time. Got audited the next year.

171
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:51,264
Sister, I'm gonna let this one slide.

172
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:53,433
- But keep your speed down.
- Yes, sir.

173
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:13,494
On Friday night, Walter Delacroix,
age 17, and Hope Percy, 18,

174
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:15,330
had been just two happy people

175
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:17,665
celebrating one of
life's turning points.

176
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,335
The couple was shot twice at close range

177
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:22,712
in the back of the head
with a .22 rifle.

178
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:26,925
Poncelet and Vitello also face
six counts of aggravated kidnapping

179
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:29,636
and one charge of aggravated rape.

180
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,513
Before the murders,

181
00:15:32,681 --> 00:15:36,976
the men allegedly had cut a path
of terror across the area.

182
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:40,396
A police spokesman said today,
in the wake of the murders,

183
00:15:40,814 --> 00:15:43,024
Poncelet addressed the judge as "Cap"

184
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:46,861
and smirked when the jury
found him guilty of murder today.

185
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,906
Poncelet claims Vitello
killed both of them.

186
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:54,494
- Y'all think he's lyin'.
- Vitello accuses Poncelet.

187
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:58,456
Both say the other did the actual
killing. Somebody's lyin' to somebody.

188
00:15:58,624 --> 00:16:00,625
They were both there.
We know that much.

189
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:03,044
How is it possible one guy gets life,
the other death?

190
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:07,173
Well, the State has probably got
a stronger case against Poncelet.

191
00:16:07,341 --> 00:16:11,636
Vitello had a better lawyer. Created
a reasonable doubt in the jury's mind.

192
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:14,847
- And Vitello gets life, Poncelet death.
- Yeah.

193
00:16:15,015 --> 00:16:16,432
Bad luck.

194
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:20,019
He needs help, Sister.

195
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:24,941
There's this lawyer, Hilton Barber.
He's aware of the case and told me no.

196
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:29,445
- Maybe you can change his mind.
- With the aim of gettin' him out?

197
00:16:29,613 --> 00:16:32,240
I'm not sure I wanna run
into this guy on the street.

198
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:35,201
There's no way he's gettin' off.
He was there. He was an accomplice.

199
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:37,078
That's life!

200
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:40,581
A life sentence in a
Louisiana prison is for real.

201
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:43,251
You're just tryin' to stop
the State from killin' him.

202
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:49,674
You want out? That's cool with me.

203
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:52,593
You don't have to go back there.

204
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:56,681
Get tough on sentencin'.
Get tough on lenient parole boards.

205
00:16:56,849 --> 00:17:00,101
Get tough on judges
who pass light sentences.

206
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:05,398
- Hello.
- Sister Helen?

207
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:08,359
- Who's this?
- Matt Poncelet, Sister.

208
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:12,822
I know I'm on death row, but there's
guys been here years and years.

209
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:15,742
I didn't know this was comin'.
They set a date.

210
00:17:15,909 --> 00:17:19,328
- What?
- They're gonna kill me on the 13th.

211
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:22,790
I didn't know you needed a lawyer
to get a pardon board hearing.

212
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:25,501
I'd do it myself if they'd let me,
but they say...

213
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:27,670
OK... OK, Matthew.

214
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:32,175
Uh... I think I know of a lawyer
that may be able to help you.

215
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:35,803
- I'll do my best, all right?
- Sister, come through for me.

216
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:39,932
You're all I got. They got me on
a greased rail to the death house here.

217
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:43,561
I ain't heard from you. You ain't
fadin' out on me, are you, Sister?

218
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:48,274
I'll get you the lawyer.
Just... try not to worry.

219
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:52,028
I'll call you soon. Bye.

220
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:54,655
It's about time the State
got with the program.

221
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:57,825
Call me sentimental,
but I'd rather see him fry.

222
00:17:57,993 --> 00:18:01,829
Barring any last-minute appeals or
stays, Poncelet will die

223
00:18:01,997 --> 00:18:05,500
under the State's new execution
procedure, the lethal injection machine.

224
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:09,337
- Hello?
- Luis, this is Helen.

225
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:12,965
Can you give me the name of that lawyer
you wanted me to talk to?

226
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:15,843
- How long you been doin' this, Sister?
- Doin' this?

227
00:18:16,011 --> 00:18:18,846
- Counseling death row inmates.
- Oh, I'm not counseling him.

228
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:22,683
- I just met him once.
- What's your impression?

229
00:18:22,851 --> 00:18:25,645
I don't know if I like him.

230
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:28,648
He needs help, but the best thing
is to bring him to you.

231
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:30,608
Well, I'll do my best.

232
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:37,156
Courts don't wanna hear appeals
on death-penalty cases.

233
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:41,786
You can have new evidence of innocence
and the court won't hear the case.

234
00:18:41,954 --> 00:18:45,373
We're the pariahs. We're...
"Have many rabbit."

235
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:48,751
Think that's a "for sale" sign
or a cry for help?

236
00:18:48,919 --> 00:18:50,878
Or is it braggin'?

237
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:57,552
Imagine that poor guy. Bought two
rabbits a year ago and now he's overrun.

238
00:18:57,719 --> 00:18:59,595
Comin' like popcorn!

239
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:06,978
The governor runs for re-election
so they set a date for my execution.

240
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:10,731
- Show how tough he is on crime.
- Matt, I agree with you.

241
00:19:10,899 --> 00:19:12,942
Politics did play a big part in this,

242
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:15,027
but don't bring it up
before the pardon board.

243
00:19:15,195 --> 00:19:16,487
Why not?

244
00:19:16,655 --> 00:19:18,489
Because it's full
of political appointees.

245
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:21,242
The last thing they wanna hear

246
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:24,537
is some convicted killer
tellin' them they is bunk.

247
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:29,250
We have to present you as a human being
and convince them to spare your life.

248
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:30,918
We have to prove I'm innocent.

249
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:34,714
We're filing appeals with
the federal and supreme courts.

250
00:19:34,882 --> 00:19:39,010
This is a pardon board. It don't matter
to them whether you pulled the trigger.

251
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:43,681
They're gonna be thinkin' of the crime,
and of you as a monster.

252
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:47,268
It's easy to kill a monster,
but it's hard to kill a human being.

253
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:51,981
We need people that know you to speak
for you. Your mama should be there.

254
00:19:52,149 --> 00:19:55,776
I don't want her there. She'll bust out
cryin' till she can't say nothin'.

255
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:58,529
Your mama should still be there.

256
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:01,532
No. She'd have to hear
the Delacroixs, the Percys, the DA.

257
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:05,119
- But if she's not at the hearing...
- Excuse me for buttin' in.

258
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:09,790
You're right. It's gonna be upsettin'
for her but... she's your mama, Matthew.

259
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:14,295
She should have the opportunity
to speak for her child.

260
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:15,755
She's just gonna blubber her head off.

261
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:19,133
Yeah, well, she has
the right to do that.

262
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:25,932
What if you die and she hasn't
had a chance to speak for you?

263
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:31,145
Don't you think it'll always eat at her,
wonderin' if she could have saved you?

264
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:40,780
I'll think about it, but I got my pride.

265
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:45,034
I ain't gonna kiss ass in front of these
people. I ain't gonna kiss nobody's ass.

266
