275
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,262
Happy Easter.

276
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:59,567
- Yes?
- Mrs. Poncelet?

277
00:21:59,735 --> 00:22:01,235
No.

278
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:04,864
Mrs. Poncelet, please.

279
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:09,035
She don't live here. Who is it?

280
00:22:09,202 --> 00:22:13,831
My name is Sister Helen Prejean.
I know your son Matthew.

281
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:19,420
Happy Easter.

282
00:22:20,630 --> 00:22:23,090
- You sure you're a sister?
- Yes.

283
00:22:24,301 --> 00:22:27,261
- You're not from the TV?
- No.

284
00:22:28,055 --> 00:22:29,805
You're sure?

285
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,770
How do you know Mattie?

286
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:38,230
I met him on death row.

287
00:22:39,316 --> 00:22:42,902
Well, you never know
who's at your front door.

288
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:46,906
So what do you want? Mattie send you
for money, for cigarettes?

289
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:49,408
No.

290
00:22:52,621 --> 00:22:54,580
So what do you want?

291
00:22:56,708 --> 00:23:00,795
You know they set the date
for Matthew's execution.

292
00:23:00,962 --> 00:23:06,550
Yeah. The prison called. Said if it
goes down, do I got death insurance.

293
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:08,177
Hah!

294
00:23:08,345 --> 00:23:11,430
What a laugh!
I ain't even got food money.

295
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:14,558
His pardon board hearing
is this Wednesday.

296
00:23:14,726 --> 00:23:18,229
His lawyer thinks it'd be
a good idea if you were there.

297
00:23:18,397 --> 00:23:20,356
What does Mattie think?

298
00:23:21,650 --> 00:23:24,652
He's worried. He wants to protect you.

299
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:27,363
Well, it's a little late for that.

300
00:23:27,531 --> 00:23:30,991
That show Inside Crime
did a thing on Mattie

301
00:23:31,159 --> 00:23:33,869
and told how I tried
to help him and everything.

302
00:23:34,037 --> 00:23:36,288
A regular Ma Barker or somethin'.

303
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:38,416
Now I'm famous.

304
00:23:38,583 --> 00:23:43,254
Yesterday I was in the store
and I see these two ladies eyein' me.

305
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:46,465
When I get closer,
I hear one of them say,

306
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:50,219
"I can't wait to hear that
they've executed that monster,

307
00:23:50,387 --> 00:23:52,721
Matthew Poncelet."

308
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:55,933
That's cruel.

309
00:23:56,685 --> 00:24:00,813
My boys are havin'
a real hard time at school.

310
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:05,526
Kids picking on 'em,
beating 'em up, calling 'em names.

311
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:09,738
Someone put a dead squirrel
in my little Troy's locker.

312
00:24:09,906 --> 00:24:13,159
Poor boy came home cryin'.

313
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:15,703
What'd he ever do to anyone?

314
00:24:19,875 --> 00:24:25,171
I just keep... tryin' to figure out
what I done wrong.

315
00:24:27,507 --> 00:24:31,552
They have been ploughed over by life.
He first got in trouble when he was 15.

316
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:34,680
- Every kid does that.
- His daddy was never around.

317
00:24:34,848 --> 00:24:38,100
Most of your kids in the project
are raised by single parents.

318
00:24:38,268 --> 00:24:43,147
They're not rapin' and killin' people.
Really, Helen, you're being suckered.

319
00:24:43,315 --> 00:24:45,399
What about the parents of these victims?

320
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:49,403
- Have you counseled them?
- You think they'd wanna talk to me?

321
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:52,823
Don't people in your neighborhood
need your help?

322
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:54,992
Yes, Mama. I'm still workin' with them.

323
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:57,995
But why are you visiting with murderers?

324
00:24:58,163 --> 00:25:00,956
For all the energy that
you're putting into them,

325
00:25:01,124 --> 00:25:04,460
you could be keepin' other kids
from going to prison.

326
00:25:04,628 --> 00:25:09,924
Mama's friends read an article which
associated your name with Poncelet.

327
00:25:10,091 --> 00:25:12,676
- My name was in the paper?
- It has nothing to do with that.

328
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:17,348
I am simply curious.
Helen, what has drawn you to this?

329
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:20,601
Mama, I don't know.

330
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:23,771
I feel caught more than drawn.

331
00:25:24,773 --> 00:25:29,485
The man's in trouble and, for some
reason, I'm the only one he trusts.

332
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:31,028
Your heart's in the right place,

333
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:34,031
but a full heart shouldn't
follow an empty head.

334
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:35,407
Or an empty stomach.

335
00:25:38,161 --> 00:25:42,122
You'd always bring home strays. If we'd
taken in all those dogs and cats,

336
00:25:42,290 --> 00:25:45,876
we wouldn't have had any money
to feed the children in this house.

337
00:25:46,836 --> 00:25:49,547
Your heart is large.

338
00:25:50,632 --> 00:25:55,678
Just take care that others don't take
advantage of it. I'd hate to see that.

339
00:25:56,638 --> 00:25:57,888
All right, Mama.

340
00:25:58,848 --> 00:26:03,060
My daddy took me to a bar when I was 12
and told me to pick my whiskey.

341
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:05,312
There was all these bottles
behind the bar.

342
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:08,983
I said "I'll take that one there
with the pretty turkey on it."

343
00:26:10,026 --> 00:26:14,738
The guys in the bar laughed their butts
off. We got drunk as coots that night.

344
00:26:14,906 --> 00:26:18,742
My daddy was a good man.
Sharecropper. Hard worker.

345
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:21,412
That's the one thing I got from him -
workin' hands.

346
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:24,999
- How old were you when he died?
- 14.

347
00:26:28,086 --> 00:26:31,463
- Why's you a nun?
- I was drawn to it, I guess.

348
00:26:31,631 --> 00:26:36,176
That's a hard question to answer. It's
like asking you why you're a convict.

349
00:26:36,344 --> 00:26:38,095
- Bad luck.
- Good luck, then.

350
00:26:38,263 --> 00:26:43,809
I had a lovin' family, a lot of support.
I felt obliged to give some of it back.

351
00:26:44,519 --> 00:26:45,978
Don't you miss havin' a man?

352
00:26:46,146 --> 00:26:48,731
Don't you wanna get married,
fall in love, have sex?

353
00:26:52,819 --> 00:26:54,403
You don't wanna talk about it?

354
00:26:55,363 --> 00:26:57,990
I have close friends - men and women.

355
00:26:58,158 --> 00:27:02,911
I've never experienced sexual intimacy,
but there's other ways of being close.

356
00:27:03,079 --> 00:27:06,498
Sharing your dreams,
your thoughts, your feelings.

357
00:27:06,666 --> 00:27:08,876
That's bein' intimate too.

358
00:27:09,044 --> 00:27:11,754
We got intimacy right now,
don't we, Sister?

359
00:27:14,758 --> 00:27:17,217
I went to see your mother.

360
00:27:17,385 --> 00:27:23,307
She said she'd appear at the pardon
board hearing if you want her to.

361
00:27:25,685 --> 00:27:28,062
I like bein' alone with you.

362
00:27:28,229 --> 00:27:30,272
You're lookin' real good to me.

363
00:27:31,733 --> 00:27:33,776
Look at you.

364
00:27:33,943 --> 00:27:36,945
Death is breathin' down your neck

365
00:27:37,113 --> 00:27:39,948
and you're playin' your little
man-on-the-make games.

366
00:27:40,909 --> 00:27:45,412
I'm not here for your amusement,
Matthew. Show some respect.

367
00:27:45,580 --> 00:27:48,707
Why should I respect you?
Cos you're a nun and you wear a cross?

368
00:27:48,875 --> 00:27:51,960
Because I'm a person.
Every person deserves respect.

369
00:27:59,594 --> 00:28:02,262
What's it gonna be with your mama?

370
00:28:03,723 --> 00:28:08,977
Mattie had a hard life,
but he was a good boy.

371
00:28:10,855 --> 00:28:12,981
When he was six, he...

372
00:28:15,944 --> 00:28:17,027
he...

373
00:28:32,419 --> 00:28:34,420
Ladies and gentlemen, let's be honest.

374
00:28:34,587 --> 00:28:37,631
You're not gonna find
many rich people on death row.

375
00:28:37,799 --> 00:28:40,718
Matthew Poncelet's here today
because he's poor.

376
00:28:40,885 --> 00:28:44,805
Didn't have money for representation,
so he took what the State gave him.

377
00:28:44,973 --> 00:28:49,393
A tax lawyer who'd never tried
a capital case before. An amateur.

378
00:28:50,145 --> 00:28:54,440
The jury selection took four hours.
The trial lasted five days.

379
00:28:54,607 --> 00:28:59,987
The lawyer raised one objection
the entire trial.

380
00:29:00,155 --> 00:29:04,158
Now, if Matthew had himself
some money,

381
00:29:04,325 --> 00:29:09,163
well, he could have hired
a team of crackerjack lawyers.

382
00:29:09,330 --> 00:29:14,126
They would have hired top-notch
investigators, a ballistics expert,

383
00:29:14,294 --> 00:29:18,338
a psychologist to compile
profiles of desirable jurors,

384
00:29:18,506 --> 00:29:24,303
and you can be sure Matthew Poncelet
wouldn't be here today, before you,

385
00:29:24,471 --> 00:29:27,514
asking for his life.

386
00:29:30,685 --> 00:29:35,147
The death penalty. It's nothing new.
Been with us for centuries.

387
00:29:35,315 --> 00:29:38,442
We've buried people alive,
lopped off their heads,

388
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:41,361
burned them alive in public squares.

389
00:29:41,529 --> 00:29:44,281
I wanted them to see this picture.

390
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:46,325
In this century, we've searched

391
00:29:46,493 --> 00:29:51,413
for more and more humane ways
of killing people we didn't like.

392
00:29:51,581 --> 00:29:55,375
We've shot 'em with firing squads,
suffocated 'em in a gas chamber.

393
00:29:55,543 --> 00:29:57,878
But now...

394
00:29:58,046 --> 00:30:03,884
Now we have developed a device
that is the most humane of all.

395
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:06,178
Lethal injection.

396
00:30:06,346 --> 00:30:08,472
We strap the guy up.

397
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:13,560
We anaesthetize him with shot No. 1.
Then shot No. 2 implodes his lungs

398
00:30:13,728 --> 00:30:17,523
and shot No. 3 stops his heart.

399
00:30:17,690 --> 00:30:21,193
We put him to death
just like an old horse.

400
00:30:21,361 --> 00:30:26,907
His face just goes to sleep. Inside, his
organs are going through Armageddon.

401
00:30:27,075 --> 00:30:29,535
The muscles of his face
would twist and contort and pull,

402
00:30:29,702 --> 00:30:34,748
but you see, shot No. 1 relaxes those
muscles so we don't see any horror show.

403
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:37,751
We don't have to taste
the blood of revenge on our lips,

404
00:30:37,919 --> 00:30:43,090
while this human being's organs
writhe, twist, contort.

405
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:49,638
We just sit there quietly, nod our
heads, and say "Justice has been done."

406
00:30:52,308 --> 00:30:58,272
It is six years since the brutal murders
of Hope Percy and Walter Delacroix.

407
00:30:58,439 --> 00:31:01,483
Justice is long past due.

408
00:31:01,651 --> 00:31:05,028
Matt Poncelet has had
a lengthy, thorough court review.

409
00:31:05,196 --> 00:31:07,531
A trial, a retrial for sentencin',

410
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:10,576
numerous appeals to
state and federal courts

411
00:31:10,743 --> 00:31:13,620
and successive petitions
filed by Mr. Barber.

412
00:31:13,788 --> 00:31:18,709
There has been no doubt in the court's
mind about who did the murder.

413
00:31:20,712 --> 00:31:25,090
Matthew Poncelet is not a good boy.
He is a heartless killer.

414
00:31:25,258 --> 00:31:29,303
These murders were calculated,
disgusting and cruel.

415
00:31:29,846 --> 00:31:34,099
This man shot Walter Delacroix
two times in the back of his head,

416
00:31:34,267 --> 00:31:36,852
then raped Hope Percy
and stabbed her 17 times

417
00:31:37,020 --> 00:31:40,397
before shootin' this sweet girl
two times in the back of the head.

418
00:31:41,733 --> 00:31:46,695
These families will never see
their children graduate from college.

419
00:31:47,989 --> 00:31:50,616
They will never attend their wedding.

420
00:31:50,783 --> 00:31:53,911
They will never have Christmas
with them again.

421
00:31:54,078 --> 00:31:56,163
There will be no grandchildren.

422
00:31:56,331 --> 00:32:02,085
All they ask of you is simple justice
for their unbearable loss.

423
00:32:02,754 --> 00:32:07,174
I ask you to take a breath,
steel your spine

424
00:32:07,342 --> 00:32:11,845
and proceed with the execution
of Matthew Poncelet.

425
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:17,351
It's always a good sign
when you have to wait.

426
00:32:17,518 --> 00:32:20,979
- I don't know if we made any headway.
- I thought you did great.

427
00:32:21,147 --> 00:32:24,232
Best thing would be if they
realized their own culpability

428
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:25,525
in the death of a man.

429
00:32:25,693 --> 00:32:28,195
- Hilton.
- Excuse me, Sister.

430
00:32:32,325 --> 00:32:34,326
I'm Walter Delacroix's father.

431
00:32:35,662 --> 00:32:37,162
Mr. Delacroix,
I'm sorry about your son.

432
00:32:37,330 --> 00:32:40,040
Sister, I'm a Catholic.

433
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:42,501
How can you sit by Poncelet's side

434
00:32:42,669 --> 00:32:45,087
without ever coming
to visit with me and my wife

435
00:32:45,254 --> 00:32:47,297
or the Percys to hear our side?

436
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:50,884
How can you spend all your time
worryin' about Poncelet

437
00:32:51,052 --> 00:32:54,304
and not think that maybe
we needed you too?

438
00:32:54,472 --> 00:32:59,559
Mr. Delacroix... I didn't think
that you wanted to... talk to me.

439
00:32:59,727 --> 00:33:01,645
Earl, are you goin' in?

440
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:04,231
This is Mary Beth and Clyde Percy.

441
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:09,027
- I'm sorry about your daughter.
- Yeah. So are we. Excuse us.

442
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:14,741
Listen, Sister.

443
00:33:14,909 --> 00:33:19,329
I'm sure you've seen a side of Matt
Poncelet that none of us has seen.

444
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:23,583
I'm sure he's on his best behavior
and must be pretty sympathetic to you.

445
00:33:23,751 --> 00:33:27,546
But, Sister, this is an evil man.

446
00:33:27,714 --> 00:33:30,674
This is a man
who abducted teenage kids

447
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:33,927
and raped... and killed them.

448
00:33:34,095 --> 00:33:38,265
That scum robbed me of my only son.

449
00:33:38,433 --> 00:33:42,394
My name... my family name dies with me.

450
00:33:42,562 --> 00:33:47,190
There will be no more Delacroixs,
Sister. No more.

451
00:33:47,358 --> 00:33:50,277
I want you to know I do care
about you and your family

452
00:33:50,445 --> 00:33:52,904
and what happened to your son.

453
00:33:53,072 --> 00:33:57,784
I'm gonna give you my number and
if there's anything that you need,

454
00:33:57,952 --> 00:34:00,537
- you just call me.
- Me call you?

455
00:34:02,582 --> 00:34:07,878
Think about that, Sister.
Think about how arrogant that is.

456
00:34:08,046 --> 00:34:10,130
Excuse me.

457
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,594
You all right?

458
00:34:17,513 --> 00:34:19,639
We better be gettin' on in.

459
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:39,326
It is the finding of this board that
clemency be denied to Matthew Poncelet.

460
00:34:39,494 --> 00:34:43,830
Execution will be carried out
as scheduled one week hence.

461
00:34:43,998 --> 00:34:45,499
Don't give up hope, Matt.

462
00:34:45,666 --> 00:34:49,252
We still got a judge
that can put a stop to this.

463
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:51,588
Then there's the US Supreme Court
and the governor.

464
00:34:51,756 --> 00:34:54,466
I'll get a private meeting.

465
00:34:55,343 --> 00:34:57,052
You're all I got, Sis.

466
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:59,346
They tell me I can have
a spiritual adviser of my choice.

467
00:34:59,514 --> 00:35:01,264
Will you do it?

468
00:35:03,559 --> 00:35:05,936
Ride along into the sunset with me.

469
00:35:10,149 --> 00:35:14,694
You're gonna have to spend several hours
with him every day as his death nears.

470
00:35:14,862 --> 00:35:19,574
And on the day of his execution you're
gonna have to spend all day with him.

471
00:35:20,576 --> 00:35:22,202
It's not an easy job.

472
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:27,040
Usually it's done by a chaplain
or a priest or a Muslim cleric.

473
00:35:29,335 --> 00:35:31,503
I want you to be realistic about this.

474
00:35:31,671 --> 00:35:36,258
We've got about a one in 1,000 chance
things might go our way.

475
00:35:36,425 --> 00:35:38,301
It's a tough road.

476
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:47,686
If that had been a king,
you could have gone back over again.

477
00:35:47,854 --> 00:35:51,565
You can jump three this way,
then go all the way back.

478
00:35:51,732 --> 00:35:54,985
She got that big old bad joker
and she don't wanna put it down.

479
00:35:55,153 --> 00:35:58,071
All right. My turn. My turn.

480
00:35:58,239 --> 00:36:00,782
I got an ace. I'm really lucky.

481
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:03,743
Whose was this?

482
00:36:04,370 --> 00:36:05,704
Oh, please don't kill him.

483
00:36:05,872 --> 00:36:09,541
He's a child of God.
He's a poet, blah, blah, blah.

484
00:36:09,709 --> 00:36:13,044
Attention all ye advocates
of killers and child molesters,

485
00:36:13,212 --> 00:36:15,130
ye opponents of execution.

486
00:36:15,298 --> 00:36:17,716
Ye cannot walk upon the high ground.

487
00:36:17,884 --> 00:36:20,844
Ye do not have
the moral authority to walk there.

488
00:36:21,012 --> 00:36:23,763
Ye traverse with scum
and scum is where ye...

489
00:36:38,237 --> 00:36:39,321
What do you want?

490
00:36:39,488 --> 00:36:41,573
Mr. Delacroix,
forgive me for intrudin',

491
00:36:41,741 --> 00:36:44,910
but I haven't been able to get
you and your wife out of my mind.

492
00:36:45,077 --> 00:36:49,289
I've been tryin' to call you
but there's been no answer.

493
00:36:49,457 --> 00:36:51,458
Can I please speak with you?

494
00:36:52,418 --> 00:36:53,418
Sure.

495
00:36:58,257 --> 00:37:02,427
I'm really sorry for not comin' to visit
with you and your wife before this.

496
00:37:02,595 --> 00:37:07,474
But... I've never been involved
in anything like this before.

497
00:37:07,642 --> 00:37:09,434
Truth is you're scared.

498
00:37:11,062 --> 00:37:12,979
Yes.

499
00:37:14,023 --> 00:37:15,565
I'd be too.

500
00:37:17,151 --> 00:37:19,569
- Come in.
- Thank you.

501
00:37:22,782 --> 00:37:26,910
Sister... Can I ask you a question?

502
00:37:29,163 --> 00:37:32,832
- Are you a communist?
- Communist? No.

503
00:37:34,168 --> 00:37:39,172
That's what some people are sayin'
with you defendin' this murderer.

504
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:43,677
But I didn't think so. Sit down.

505
00:37:43,844 --> 00:37:45,553
Thank you.

506
00:37:50,685 --> 00:37:54,229
- Care for some coffee?
- Thank you.

507
00:37:56,691 --> 00:37:58,108
Sorry about the mess.

508
00:38:00,695 --> 00:38:03,363
My wife and I had a big fight.

509
00:38:03,531 --> 00:38:05,865
When we got back from the hearing,

510
00:38:06,033 --> 00:38:10,328
she... took Walter's clothes
out of his closet.

511
00:38:10,496 --> 00:38:14,708
Put 'em in boxes. Called Goodwill.

512
00:38:16,002 --> 00:38:20,005
She says she wants to
put the past behind her.

513
00:38:20,172 --> 00:38:24,509
She says she...
has to move on in her life.

514
00:38:26,637 --> 00:38:31,016
- She's not herself.
- That must be so hard.

515
00:38:32,351 --> 00:38:37,856
When it first happened, she had me bring
her to Walter's grave every morning.

516
00:38:40,192 --> 00:38:42,027
She wept a river, poor woman.

517
00:38:42,903 --> 00:38:47,324
Whole days, nights... for weeks, months.

518
00:38:48,909 --> 00:38:54,914
I wish there was some way,
some key into the past, to change it.

519
00:38:58,085 --> 00:38:59,919
It tears me up.

520
00:39:04,425 --> 00:39:06,009
She used to be a ball.

521
00:39:08,346 --> 00:39:11,639
We would have us
some fun, boy.

522
00:39:12,933 --> 00:39:14,851
Some times.

523
00:39:17,271 --> 00:39:21,191
Laugh... Laugh our heads off.

524
00:39:33,537 --> 00:39:37,791
Walter learned to walk
on this floor right here.

525
00:39:45,174 --> 00:39:48,635
He bust his chin on the arm
of that sofa right there.

526
00:39:52,431 --> 00:39:54,391
In that love seat right there,

527
00:39:56,060 --> 00:40:01,481
he sat with Hope...
the week before they died.

528
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:11,533
When you lose a child

529
00:40:11,700 --> 00:40:15,787
all the memories,
get sealed in a place.

530
00:40:16,956 --> 00:40:18,665
Sealed.

531
00:40:20,543 --> 00:40:24,129
Like a... shrine.

532
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:42,230
So, you've put in a request to be the
spiritual adviser to Matthew Poncelet.

533
00:40:42,398 --> 00:40:43,356
Yes, Father.

534
00:40:43,524 --> 00:40:46,860
- Why?
- He asked me.

535
00:40:47,027 --> 00:40:49,279
This is highly unusual.

536
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:53,032
- Why?
- You would be the first woman to do it.

537
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:54,409
Really?

538
00:40:54,577 --> 00:40:58,288
This kind of situation
requires an experienced hand.

539
00:40:58,456 --> 00:41:03,668
This boy is to be executed in six days
and is in dire need of redemption.

540
00:41:03,836 --> 00:41:06,796
Are you up to this?

541
00:41:07,882 --> 00:41:12,177
I don't know, Father. I hope so.
I've been prayin' for guidance.

542
00:41:12,970 --> 00:41:14,929
You can save this boy

543
00:41:15,097 --> 00:41:19,559
by getting him to receive the
sacraments of the Church before he dies.

544
00:41:19,727 --> 00:41:24,230
This is your job.
Nothing more, nothing less.

545
00:41:25,649 --> 00:41:29,819
If you need any help,
please feel free to call on me.

546
00:41:29,987 --> 00:41:31,446
Thank you, Father.

547
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:35,742
I don't wanna be buried here.

548
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:39,204
They said they'd call Mama and
ask her about the funeral arrangements.

549
00:41:39,371 --> 00:41:41,581
Could you do that?
She'd fall apart on 'em.

550
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:43,374
I'll do it.

551
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:50,173
You ever read the Bible?

552
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:51,341
Yes, ma'am.

553
00:41:51,509 --> 00:41:54,594
I ain't much of a Bible reader,
but I pick it up from time to time.

554
00:41:54,762 --> 00:41:57,263
Like WC Fields read his Bible.

555
00:41:57,431 --> 00:41:59,265
- Who?
- WC Fields.

556
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:01,601
Played this drunken character
in the movies.

557
00:42:01,769 --> 00:42:05,855
He's on his deathbed and a friend
comes and sees him readin' the Bible.

558
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:11,277
The friend says "WC, you don't believe
in God. Why are you reading the Bible?"

559
00:42:11,445 --> 00:42:15,657
And Fields says
"I'm lookin' for a loophole."

560
00:42:20,287 --> 00:42:22,747
I ain't lookin' for no loophole.

561
00:42:24,625 --> 00:42:26,668
Rain, rain, rain.

562
00:42:27,378 --> 00:42:31,673
That's a bad sign. They already
executed one black - Tobias.

563
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:35,301
Wayne Purcell tonight.
That's two blacks.

564
00:42:36,637 --> 00:42:40,473
Time for a white. The governor's
under pressure to get a white.

565
00:42:40,641 --> 00:42:42,433
And that's me!

566
00:42:43,936 --> 00:42:48,147
Nigger on the gurney before me. I hope
they clean it before they put me on it.

567
00:42:50,651 --> 00:42:52,819
Was your daddy a racist?

568
00:42:52,987 --> 00:42:56,823
- What kind of question is that?
- You have to teach a child to hate.

569
00:42:56,991 --> 00:42:59,659
- I just don't like niggers.
- Have you known any black people?

570
00:42:59,827 --> 00:43:02,996
They was all around when I was a kid.
Lived around me.

571
00:43:03,163 --> 00:43:07,166
- Did you ever play with a black child?
- No. Me and my cousin got jumped once.

572
00:43:07,334 --> 00:43:10,003
- What happened?
- We was throwin' rocks at 'em.

573
00:43:10,170 --> 00:43:13,590
Next day they wait their chance,
get ahold of our bikes, tear 'em up.

574
00:43:13,757 --> 00:43:15,675
- Can you blame 'em?
- No.

575
00:43:15,843 --> 00:43:19,762
But slavery's long over. They always
sayin' what a bad deal they got.

576
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:23,725
- The kids that tore up your bike?
- I can't stand people who are victims.

577
00:43:23,892 --> 00:43:25,977
- Victims.
- Yeah. They all victims.

578
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:30,607
I don't know any victims in my area.
I know some decent, hard-workin' people.

579
00:43:30,774 --> 00:43:33,943
I know a lot of lazy coloreds
suckin' up tax dollars.

580
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:36,696
- You sound like a politician.
- What's that mean?

581
00:43:36,864 --> 00:43:40,700
- You ever been the object of prejudice?
- No.

582
00:43:40,868 --> 00:43:43,494
What do people think about
inmates on death row?

583
00:43:43,662 --> 00:43:45,872
- Why don't you tell me?
- They're all monsters.

584
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:49,459
Disposable human waste
suckin' up tax dollars.

585
00:43:49,627 --> 00:43:51,711
They gonna kill me. I'm innocent.

586
00:43:51,879 --> 00:43:55,548
I ain't whinin'. I ain't sittin' on no
porch going "Slavery, slavery."

587
00:43:55,716 --> 00:44:00,803
I like rebels. Martin Luther King,
he led his people all the way to DC.

588
00:44:00,971 --> 00:44:04,057
- You respect Martin Luther King?
- He put up a fight, wasn't lazy.

589
00:44:04,224 --> 00:44:05,808
- What about lazy whites?
- Don't like 'em.

590
00:44:05,976 --> 00:44:08,311
So it's lazy people you don't like.

591
00:44:08,479 --> 00:44:10,647
Can we talk about somethin' else?

592
00:44:24,953 --> 00:44:28,456
Jesus also said "He who lives
by the sword shall die by the sword."

593
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:31,250
Purcell had it coming to him.
He had it coming!

594
00:44:31,418 --> 00:44:35,463
Nine, eight, seven, six,

595
00:44:35,631 --> 00:44:38,800
five, four, three,

596
00:44:38,967 --> 00:44:41,427
two, one.

597
00:44:50,896 --> 00:44:54,232
It's the only way we can be sure
that they will not kill again.

598
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,693
Life without parole. Oh, sure!

599
00:44:56,860 --> 00:45:00,822
How many prison guards and prisoners
do they have to kill before it's over?

600
00:45:00,989 --> 00:45:05,284
These people are mad dogs. Maniacs.

601
00:45:06,620 --> 00:45:08,037
Come on. Let's go.

602
00:45:13,961 --> 00:45:17,213
If the governor and the courts
turn us down,

603
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:20,675
Matt's gonna be dead in six days.

604
00:45:22,469 --> 00:45:27,265
We gotta get us a funeral home
and... someplace to bury him.

605
00:45:28,559 --> 00:45:32,186
Maybe our sisters will donate
one of their burial plots.

606
00:45:32,354 --> 00:45:34,272
Somebody to do the burial service.

607
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:38,151
Clothes. I guess... a suit.

608
00:45:38,318 --> 00:45:39,944
A suit?

609
00:45:41,989 --> 00:45:44,741
What size suit do you think he wears?

610
00:45:45,909 --> 00:45:47,702
I don't know.

611
00:45:49,329 --> 00:45:51,038
How tall is he?

612
00:45:53,167 --> 00:45:56,627
I don't know. I think he's... kinda big.

613
00:45:56,795 --> 00:46:02,467
What... size is kinda big?
Does it run like big, medium and petite?

614
00:46:08,348 --> 00:46:12,143
Well, I don't know.
I never bought a man's suit before.

615
00:46:13,270 --> 00:46:18,524
Won't you be a pretty sight?
A nun shoppin' for a man's suit!

616
00:46:21,236 --> 00:46:26,032
I'm out of my league.
This is so surreal.

617
00:46:29,286 --> 00:46:32,371
Hope had just graduated
from high school in early May.

618
00:46:32,539 --> 00:46:37,168
She was to join the air force
on June 15th.

619
00:46:37,336 --> 00:46:39,170
That's the day it happened.

620
00:46:39,338 --> 00:46:41,672
She almost got out of Slidell.

621
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:44,675
She was hopin'
to get stationed overseas.

622
00:46:44,843 --> 00:46:50,598
She liked to travel and loved being
around people of different cultures.

623
00:46:51,725 --> 00:46:56,479
On June 15th, the recruiting sergeant
was to meet Hope in Slidell

624
00:46:56,647 --> 00:46:59,899
and drive her to Baton Rouge
for induction.

625
00:47:00,067 --> 00:47:03,486
The day before I took her shoppin'
for things she'd need.

626
00:47:03,654 --> 00:47:06,155
You know, just practical things.

627
00:47:07,157 --> 00:47:11,077
That evening about five, she dressed
and headed off to work at Coreys

628
00:47:11,245 --> 00:47:13,204
where she waitressed.

629
00:47:13,372 --> 00:47:16,415
After work she had a date with Walter.

630
00:47:17,125 --> 00:47:23,089
As she was about to leave, the hem
of her skirt was comin' out and I...

631
00:47:24,007 --> 00:47:26,342
She was in such a hurry, so...

632
00:47:26,510 --> 00:47:30,429
I pinned it for her with one
of those tiny safety pins

633
00:47:30,597 --> 00:47:33,599
and she was gone, out the door.

634
00:47:33,934 --> 00:47:36,227
You don't know, when
you see your child leave,

635
00:47:36,395 --> 00:47:40,314
that you're never gonna
see them alive again.

636
00:47:41,525 --> 00:47:43,901
If I'd known that,

637
00:47:44,945 --> 00:47:48,072
I would have told her
how much I love her.

638
00:47:48,615 --> 00:47:51,450
You know, my last words to her,

639
00:47:51,618 --> 00:47:54,745
the last that
she ever heard from me,

640
00:47:54,913 --> 00:47:58,040
were about the hem of her skirt.

641
00:48:00,294 --> 00:48:03,212
Next morning we waited for her
to come out of that door.

642
00:48:04,756 --> 00:48:07,592
This was Hope's big day.

643
00:48:07,759 --> 00:48:10,261
Our baby was leavin' home.

644
00:48:10,429 --> 00:48:16,142
Her room was empty
and the bed was still neatly made.

645
00:48:16,310 --> 00:48:19,937
So I telephoned the Delacroixs.

646
00:48:20,105 --> 00:48:25,276
Our hearts sank when they told us that
Walter hadn't come home that night too.

647
00:48:25,444 --> 00:48:29,113
And then for one brief moment
we thought, well,

648
00:48:30,949 --> 00:48:33,618
maybe they'd run off
and gotten married or somethin'.

649
00:48:34,369 --> 00:48:39,332
But we knew that she was
just too sensible a girl to do that.

650
00:48:39,499 --> 00:48:43,377
I went down to the police
and filled out a missing person's form.

651
00:48:44,379 --> 00:48:48,841
Three days later,
the sheriff formed a search party.

652
00:48:49,384 --> 00:48:52,345
- I went along with 'em.
- They were gone all day.

653
00:48:52,512 --> 00:48:55,348
They just walked for miles and nothin'.

654
00:48:55,515 --> 00:48:58,559
On Thursday, June 20th,

655
00:48:58,727 --> 00:49:03,856
some kids were walking near
Flank's Cove and they found a purse,

656
00:49:04,024 --> 00:49:07,985
some clothing and a wallet.
They turned them in to the police.

657
00:49:08,904 --> 00:49:14,909
They found the kids' bodies on Friday,
six days after they'd gone missin'.

658
00:49:16,828 --> 00:49:22,541
My daughter's body
was nude, legs spread-eagled.

659
00:49:23,293 --> 00:49:27,755
The coroner's report said that
her vagina was all tore up.

660
00:49:29,716 --> 00:49:32,635
At first they couldn't find
this class pin she was wearin'

661
00:49:32,803 --> 00:49:37,223
cos it was embedded so deep
from the stabbin'.

662
00:49:38,725 --> 00:49:43,896
She loved that pin. She was so proud
of it. She wore it all the time.

663
00:49:44,064 --> 00:49:48,567
It said "Class of '88.
Making a difference."

664
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:53,197
The police wouldn't
let us identify the body.

665
00:49:53,365 --> 00:49:56,158
They said it would be too traumatic.

666
00:49:56,326 --> 00:50:02,123
I just couldn't bear the thought
of them buryin' that body

667
00:50:02,290 --> 00:50:06,919
without makin' absolutely and
positively sure that that was Hope.

668
00:50:07,087 --> 00:50:09,588
So I called my brother. He's a dentist.

669
00:50:09,756 --> 00:50:14,844
I asked him to go to the funeral home
and make an ID from dental records.

670
00:50:15,762 --> 00:50:20,683
Before he'd stuck his hand into
that bag with all that lime in it

671
00:50:20,851 --> 00:50:24,186
and fished Hope's jaw out,

672
00:50:24,354 --> 00:50:27,690
he'd been against the death penalty.

673
00:50:27,858 --> 00:50:31,485
And after that he was all for it.

674
00:50:31,653 --> 00:50:35,531
I knew it had to be Hope.

675
00:50:35,699 --> 00:50:40,745
That's what my mind told me,
you know, but I... just had to be sure.

676
00:50:53,008 --> 00:50:56,927
OK. This is Sister Helen Prejean.

677
00:50:57,095 --> 00:51:00,014
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you, Emily.

678
00:51:00,807 --> 00:51:02,433
OK?

679
00:51:03,143 --> 00:51:07,271
OK. Let's go in the kitchen.
I'll make us some coffee.

680
00:51:17,115 --> 00:51:21,410
I met Poncelet face to face
in the hallway during the trial.

681
00:51:21,578 --> 00:51:23,746
I ain't gonna get no chair, Daddy.

682
00:51:23,914 --> 00:51:27,458
You're gonna fry.
And I'm gonna watch you sizzle.

683
00:51:28,460 --> 00:51:31,504
There was a sheriff
standin' pretty close by me.

684
00:51:31,671 --> 00:51:35,841
I could have grabbed his gun.
I could have shot Poncelet right there.

685
00:51:36,009 --> 00:51:40,012
I could have killed him on that day.
I wished I would have.

686
00:51:40,180 --> 00:51:43,432
I'd be a happier man today.

687
00:51:47,187 --> 00:51:50,106
So what made you change your mind?

688
00:51:50,273 --> 00:51:54,360
- Change my mind?
- What made you come round to our side?

689
00:52:02,702 --> 00:52:05,204
I just... wanted to come and see

690
00:52:05,372 --> 00:52:09,041
if I could help y'all and pray with you.

691
00:52:09,209 --> 00:52:10,751
Thank you.

692
00:52:12,295 --> 00:52:14,088
But...

693
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:22,388
He asked me to be his spiritual adviser,
to be with him when he dies.

694
00:52:22,556 --> 00:52:25,015
And what did you say?

695
00:52:26,476 --> 00:52:28,310
That I would.

696
00:52:29,396 --> 00:52:31,480
We thought you'd changed your mind.

697
00:52:32,566 --> 00:52:34,358
We thought that's why you were here.

698
00:52:37,946 --> 00:52:39,655
No.

699
00:52:42,659 --> 00:52:45,911
- How can you come here?
- How can you do that?

700
00:52:46,079 --> 00:52:49,248
How can you sit with that scum?

701
00:52:49,416 --> 00:52:53,085
Mr. Percy, I've never
done this before. I'm...

702
00:52:53,253 --> 00:52:55,546
I'm tryin'...

703
00:52:56,590 --> 00:53:00,593
I'm just tryin' to follow
the example of Jesus,

704
00:53:00,760 --> 00:53:06,640
who said that every person
is worth more than their worst act.

705
00:53:06,808 --> 00:53:10,186
This is not a person. This is an animal.

706
00:53:10,353 --> 00:53:14,398
No, I take that back. Animals don't
rape and murder their own kind.

707
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:18,277
Matthew Poncelet is God's mistake.

708
00:53:18,445 --> 00:53:22,656
And you want to hold
the poor murderer's hand?

709
00:53:22,824 --> 00:53:25,409
You wanna be there
to comfort him when he dies?

710
00:53:25,577 --> 00:53:28,287
There wasn't anybody
in the woods to comfort Hope

711
00:53:28,455 --> 00:53:31,874
when those two animals pushed her
face down into the wet grass!

712
00:53:32,042 --> 00:53:36,879
I just wanna help him
take responsibility for what he did.

713
00:53:37,047 --> 00:53:40,591
Does he admit to what he did?
Is he sorry?

714
00:53:40,759 --> 00:53:45,471
- He says he didn't kill anybody.
- Sister, you're in way over your head.

715
00:53:45,639 --> 00:53:49,016
You don't know what it's like
to carry a child and give birth

716
00:53:49,184 --> 00:53:53,145
and get up with a sick child
in the middle of the night.

717
00:53:53,313 --> 00:53:55,773
You say your prayers
and get a good night's sleep.

718
00:53:55,941 --> 00:53:59,235
My parents raised me
to respect the religious.

719
00:53:59,402 --> 00:54:02,404
Sister, I think you need
to leave this house right now.

720
00:54:03,615 --> 00:54:05,366
I'm sorry.

721
00:54:05,700 --> 00:54:07,326
Wait a minute.

722
00:54:07,494 --> 00:54:11,747
If you really are sorry and you
really do care about this family,

723
00:54:11,915 --> 00:54:14,500
you'd wanna see justice done
for our murdered child.

724
00:54:14,668 --> 00:54:16,794
You can't have it both ways.

725
00:54:16,962 --> 00:54:20,673
You can't befriend that murderer
and expect to be our friend too.

726
00:54:20,840 --> 00:54:24,635
You brought the enemy
into this house, Sister. You gotta go.

727
00:54:36,231 --> 00:54:39,900
I come from a good family.
My family can't be blamed for nothin'.

728
00:54:40,068 --> 00:54:43,153
I had two families.
Both of 'em I'd live and die for.

729
00:54:43,321 --> 00:54:47,408
- Your other family is?
- The family of man. Of men in prison.

730
00:54:47,575 --> 00:54:49,702
My white family, the Aryan brotherhood.

731
00:54:49,869 --> 00:54:52,538
You're a white supremacist,
a follower of Hitler?

732
00:54:52,706 --> 00:54:55,708
Hitler was a leader. I admire him
for gettin' things done.

733
00:54:55,875 --> 00:55:00,129
Like Castro. Hitler might have gone
overboard with the killin' stuff,

734
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:02,673
but he was on the right track
about the Aryan race.

735
00:55:02,841 --> 00:55:05,384
The right track?
The murder of six million Jews?

736
00:55:05,552 --> 00:55:06,552
That's never been proven.

737
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:09,680
What am I doin' with this guy?
I'm nuts.

738
00:55:11,141 --> 00:55:14,560
...political assassination
of Castro, Allende, Sandinistas...

739
00:55:16,104 --> 00:55:17,938
The government shouldn't...

740
00:55:18,106 --> 00:55:20,274
- Hello?
- Sister? Hilton Barber.

741
00:55:20,442 --> 00:55:23,527
We need you to come in
for a strategy meeting.

742
00:55:24,821 --> 00:55:26,530
In the Shreveport Times,

743
00:55:26,698 --> 00:55:29,408
Poncelet says that if he
had to do it all over again,

744
00:55:29,576 --> 00:55:35,497
he would do something useful like
bombing government buildings.

745
00:55:35,665 --> 00:55:38,167
We must get him off
this political prisoner kick.

746
00:55:38,335 --> 00:55:41,253
Henry, how close are we
on the supreme court docket?

747
00:55:41,421 --> 00:55:44,548
- A couple of days.
- We don't have a couple of days!

748
00:55:44,716 --> 00:55:47,926
- We don't have the legal staff, Hilton.
- You've had it three days.

749
00:55:48,094 --> 00:55:51,930
- Where were you yesterday anyway?
- I had to take my kid to the dentist.

750
00:55:52,098 --> 00:55:53,932
A man's gonna die on death row and...

751
00:55:54,100 --> 00:55:56,352
My kid needed to
hold her daddy's hand.

752
00:55:56,519 --> 00:56:01,190
If you don't like it, find another
lawyer to volunteer his time.

753
00:56:07,864 --> 00:56:10,449
People are thinkin'
you're some kind of a nut.

754
00:56:10,617 --> 00:56:14,787
Admirin' Hitler and wantin' to come back
as a terrorist and blow people up!

755
00:56:14,954 --> 00:56:17,581
I didn't say people.
Government buildings, not people.

756
00:56:17,749 --> 00:56:20,042
How can you bomb a building
without hurtin' somebody?

757
00:56:20,210 --> 00:56:22,836
I ain't got no love
for the US government.

758
00:56:23,004 --> 00:56:27,049
You're a fool. You are makin' it
so easy for them to kill you.

759
00:56:27,217 --> 00:56:32,471
Comin' across as a crazed, animal, Nazi,
racist, mad dog who deserves to die.

760
00:56:32,639 --> 00:56:33,847
Is that what you think?

761
00:56:34,015 --> 00:56:36,058
You are makin' it
so difficult to help you.

762
00:56:36,226 --> 00:56:38,977
- You can leave.
- I'm not gonna do that.

763
00:56:40,897 --> 00:56:43,857
It's up to you.
You want me to go, you say so.

764
00:56:51,324 --> 00:56:53,575
Do you ever think about those kids?

765
00:56:53,743 --> 00:56:55,702
It's terrible what
happened to them kids.

766
00:56:55,870 --> 00:56:57,996
It didn't have to happen.

767
00:56:58,164 --> 00:57:01,708
Do you ever think about what
you and Vitello did to their parents?

768
00:57:01,876 --> 00:57:05,170
It's hard to have sympathy for them
when they want to kill me.

769
00:57:05,338 --> 00:57:10,092
Well, think about it.
Their kids are shot, stabbed, raped,

770
00:57:10,260 --> 00:57:13,095
left in the woods to die alone.

771
00:57:13,263 --> 00:57:16,432
What if it happened to your mama
or your little brother?

772
00:57:16,599 --> 00:57:20,060
- What would you wanna do to them?
- I'd sure as hell wanna kill 'em.

773
00:57:20,228 --> 00:57:23,730
I understand them parents,
but they callin' for the wrong head.

774
00:57:23,898 --> 00:57:25,983
- I wanna take a lie detector test.
- What?

775
00:57:26,151 --> 00:57:31,572
It won't change their minds, but I want
my mama to know I didn't kill any kids.

776
00:57:40,165 --> 00:57:42,166
Boy, that's good.

777
00:57:47,005 --> 00:57:50,966
Hey, y'all! Havin' a party! Palmer.

778
00:57:51,134 --> 00:57:54,470
- Herbie, how's your side feelin'?
- OK.

779
00:57:54,637 --> 00:57:56,597
- Kenitra, how are you doin'?
- Fine.

780
00:57:56,764 --> 00:58:00,267
- Come on, Kenitra. Let's go.
- Bye-bye.

781
00:58:02,437 --> 00:58:04,104
Wait a minute. What happened?

782
00:58:06,107 --> 00:58:08,275
There's talk in the neighborhood.

783
00:58:08,443 --> 00:58:12,571
Someone read some of Poncelet's racist
comments. Your name was in the article.

784
00:58:12,739 --> 00:58:15,073
Oh, Lord.

785
00:58:15,241 --> 00:58:17,326
You haven't been at the learning centre.

786
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:20,829
They think you care more
about him than your classes.

787
00:58:23,416 --> 00:58:27,377
- Colleen, I'm so sorry.
- It's all right. I still love you.

788
00:58:28,087 --> 00:58:29,421
I just thought you should know.

789
00:58:30,507 --> 00:58:31,882
Oh!

790
00:58:33,343 --> 00:58:35,010
I got this at Goodwill.

791
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:42,726
I talked to Bishop Norwich.
He said he would say the funeral mass.

792
00:58:43,561 --> 00:58:47,356
I also found a funeral home
willing to donate their services.

793
00:58:47,524 --> 00:58:52,069
The leaders of the congregation met and
we can use one of our own burial plots.

794
00:58:52,779 --> 00:58:57,366
If Matt dies, guess who
he'll be buried next to.

795
00:58:57,534 --> 00:59:00,536
- Who was the last person to die?
- Sister Celestine.

796
00:59:02,121 --> 00:59:03,205
Oh, Lord.

797
00:59:03,373 --> 00:59:07,459
Remember when that sweet little girl
came to introduce her husband to us?

798
00:59:07,627 --> 00:59:11,463
Sister Celestine said "I'm glad I'll
never have to share my bed with a man."

799
00:59:11,631 --> 00:59:14,800
- She loved her celibacy so much.
- I know.

800
00:59:14,968 --> 00:59:19,388
She's gonna be lyin' next to a man
for all eternity.

801
00:59:36,406 --> 00:59:40,409
My daughter's killer can possibly
get out on parole in another year.

802
00:59:41,536 --> 00:59:43,662
He's only served six.

803
00:59:45,415 --> 00:59:48,166
I can't bear the thought
of him bein' a free man

804
00:59:48,334 --> 00:59:52,296
and her buried in the ground
and dead for ever.

805
00:59:53,631 --> 00:59:57,301
...was killed by her ex-husband.

806
00:59:57,468 --> 01:00:02,764
...stabbed to death
in our backyard by my son's best friend.

807
01:00:02,932 --> 01:00:04,349
He'd spent the night at our house

808
01:00:04,517 --> 01:00:07,686
and gone to church with us
that very morning.

809
01:00:08,313 --> 01:00:10,564
I've just lost my child.

810
01:00:12,942 --> 01:00:18,780
When our child was killed,
it took over a week to find her body.

811
01:00:19,949 --> 01:00:24,202
The DA's office treated us
like we were the criminals.

812
01:00:24,370 --> 01:00:29,583
My wife...
filed for divorce this afternoon.

813
01:00:31,753 --> 01:00:36,965
We just have different ways
of dealing with our son's death.

814
01:00:39,927 --> 01:00:42,554
"Until death do us part."

815
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:47,142
We're nothin' special.

816
01:00:47,310 --> 01:00:50,562
Most folks that lose a kid split up.

817
01:00:50,730 --> 01:00:53,357
70% or somethin'.

818
01:00:53,524 --> 01:00:56,777
I just wish I could laugh,
find somethin' funny.

819
01:00:58,529 --> 01:01:00,238
This is my car.

820
01:01:01,783 --> 01:01:04,409
Thanks for invitin' me, Mr. Delacroix.

821
01:01:06,454 --> 01:01:08,288
You take care, Sister.

822
01:01:59,048 --> 01:02:02,342
What the fuck you doin'? What you doin'?

823
01:02:38,296 --> 01:02:39,880
Raise your arms.

824
01:02:44,051 --> 01:02:45,427
Go ahead.

825
01:02:49,182 --> 01:02:50,682
Have a seat in that chair.

826
01:03:10,495 --> 01:03:12,204
Like my new digs?

827
01:03:14,540 --> 01:03:15,707
Hi.

828
01:03:19,545 --> 01:03:21,379
I'm pretty special.

829
01:03:22,215 --> 01:03:25,258
I'm pretty special.
Have this place all to myself.

830
01:03:28,054 --> 01:03:30,347
They got ten guards guardin' me.

831
01:03:31,641 --> 01:03:34,726
Got one guy that comes down every 15
minutes just to see if I killed myself.

832
01:03:34,894 --> 01:03:37,229
Suicide watch.

833
01:03:39,607 --> 01:03:43,401
Never had so many people
carin' about what I was doin'.

834
01:03:44,070 --> 01:03:46,571
When did they bring you here?

835
01:03:46,739 --> 01:03:49,699
Last night. Late.

836
01:03:49,867 --> 01:03:53,662
Didn't say goodbye to most of the guys
on the row. They were asleep.

837
01:03:53,830 --> 01:03:56,248
Did you take care of
that lie detector test yet?

838
01:03:56,415 --> 01:04:00,252
I made some calls,
but I haven't had any luck yet.

839
01:04:03,840 --> 01:04:07,926
So this is the end, huh?
My death-house vacation.

840
01:04:08,094 --> 01:04:11,721
Three days of quiet.
Plenty of time to read my Bible.

841
01:04:11,889 --> 01:04:17,269
Look for a loophole.

842
01:04:22,483 --> 01:04:25,569
Did you read anythin'
about Jesus in that Bible?

843
01:04:28,322 --> 01:04:33,285
Uh... Holy man. Did good. In heaven.

844
01:04:34,370 --> 01:04:35,495
Praise Jesus.

845
01:04:37,123 --> 01:04:40,041
There are some passages in there

846
01:04:40,209 --> 01:04:43,753
about when Jesus was facin' death
alone that you might wanna check out.

847
01:04:43,921 --> 01:04:47,257
I think me and Jesus have
a different way of dealin' with things.

848
01:04:47,425 --> 01:04:49,968
He's one of them
turn-the-other-cheek guys.

849
01:04:51,012 --> 01:04:55,265
It takes a lot of strength
to turn the other cheek.

850
01:04:55,433 --> 01:04:58,435
You say you like rebels.
What do you think Jesus was?

851
01:04:58,603 --> 01:05:01,813
- He wasn't no rebel.
- Sure he was. He was a dangerous man.

852
01:05:01,981 --> 01:05:05,734
- Why is "love your brother" dangerous?
- Because his love changed things.

853
01:05:05,902 --> 01:05:08,737
His love changed things.

854
01:05:09,363 --> 01:05:13,325
All those people nobody cared about -
prostitutes, beggars, the poor...

855
01:05:13,492 --> 01:05:16,328
...they finally had somebody
who respected them, loved them.

856
01:05:16,495 --> 01:05:19,831
Made 'em realize their own worth.

857
01:05:19,999 --> 01:05:24,878
They were becomin' so powerful that
the guys on the top got real nervous

858
01:05:25,046 --> 01:05:27,839
and so they had to kill Jesus.

859
01:05:28,883 --> 01:05:30,425
Kinda like me, huh?

860
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:36,765
No, Matt... Not at all like you.

861
01:05:36,933 --> 01:05:41,061
Jesus changed the world with his love.
You watched while two kids were killed.

862
01:05:42,772 --> 01:05:45,649
Step back from the door, Sister!

863
01:05:46,108 --> 01:05:48,151
Why? What's happenin'?

864
01:05:53,491 --> 01:05:58,078
- Move it on out, boy.
- Well, Sister... What's this?

865
01:06:01,582 --> 01:06:04,501
He'll be an hour, Sister.
Why don't you get some air?

866
01:06:04,669 --> 01:06:07,170
- Where are they takin' him?
- I can't tell you.

867
01:06:20,935 --> 01:06:25,021
Sister Helen? Chaplain Farley called.
He's at the gate. He'll be right here.

868
01:06:25,189 --> 01:06:26,398
Thank you.

869
01:06:26,565 --> 01:06:30,735
Sergeant Trapp, how long do you think
that big old tree's been there?

870
01:06:32,029 --> 01:06:34,906
Ma'am, ain't no tellin'.

871
01:06:35,950 --> 01:06:39,744
Saw you outside the gates
the other night at Purcell's execution.

872
01:06:39,912 --> 01:06:41,329
Yeah.

873
01:06:41,497 --> 01:06:44,249
- You seemed upset.
- Upset? No.

874
01:06:44,792 --> 01:06:48,378
- Were you in the room when they did it?
- I'm on the strap-down team.

875
01:06:48,546 --> 01:06:51,423
Left leg. That's my job. The left leg.

876
01:06:51,590 --> 01:06:54,759
We take the prisoner from his cell
to the execution chamber.

877
01:06:54,927 --> 01:07:00,807
- Wow. That's gotta be tough.
- It's hard. I didn't sleep that night.

878
01:07:01,892 --> 01:07:04,686
I think it's gotta affect
everybody that sees it,

879
01:07:04,854 --> 01:07:06,563
whether they're for it or against it.

880
01:07:06,731 --> 01:07:11,526
It's just part of the job. These
prisoners get what's comin' to 'em.

881
01:07:11,694 --> 01:07:16,906
It's easy for someone to come in here
and make a rash judgment on procedure.

882
01:07:17,074 --> 01:07:21,494
What may appear on the surface
to be irrational or unnecessary

883
01:07:21,662 --> 01:07:27,125
proves upon examination to have solid
reasoning and experience behind it.

884
01:07:27,710 --> 01:07:31,129
Father, all I want is to play a hymn
for Matt before his execution.

885
01:07:31,297 --> 01:07:34,883
And experience tells us
that music stirs up emotion.

886
01:07:35,051 --> 01:07:39,637
Emotion that can produce
an unexpected reaction in the inmate.

887
01:07:39,805 --> 01:07:44,684
All right. Do you have any objection
to my asking the warden for his opinion?

888
01:07:46,312 --> 01:07:50,356
I would oppose it,
but you may if you like.

889
01:07:51,525 --> 01:07:54,110
Thank you. And thank you for your time.

890
01:07:54,278 --> 01:07:58,323
I understand you were protesting outside
the gates during the last execution.

891
01:07:58,491 --> 01:07:59,908
Yes.

892
01:08:00,076 --> 01:08:04,662
Are you familiar with the Old Testament?
"Thou shalt not kill."

893
01:08:04,830 --> 01:08:09,751
"If anyone sheds the blood of man,
by man shall his blood be shed."

894
01:08:09,919 --> 01:08:15,715
Yes, Father. In the New Testament, Jesus
talks about grace and reconciliation.

895
01:08:15,883 --> 01:08:20,095
Poncelet has to understand
that Jesus died for his sins.

896
01:08:20,262 --> 01:08:21,513
If he accepts that,

897
01:08:21,680 --> 01:08:26,643
reconciliation is his and
his soul shall have eternal life.

898
01:08:26,811 --> 01:08:31,022
One's opinion of the death penalty
is not the issue here.

899
01:08:31,732 --> 01:08:37,195
Look at Romans. "Let every person be
subordinate to the higher authorities.

900
01:08:37,363 --> 01:08:40,949
For there is no authority
except from God.

901
01:08:41,117 --> 01:08:45,703
And those who oppose it
will bring judgment upon themselves."

902
01:08:46,455 --> 01:08:48,456
- What is it?
- She collapsed in my office.

903
01:08:48,624 --> 01:08:51,376
- She's havin' a heart attack.
- I'm OK. I just fainted.

904
01:08:53,379 --> 01:08:54,963
I just need something to eat.

905
01:09:02,888 --> 01:09:05,598
Could you tell Matt
what happened, please?

906
01:09:05,766 --> 01:09:09,018
- When we're finished here.
- No, I've gotta tell him now.

907
01:09:09,186 --> 01:09:11,855
- I'll take care of it, Sister.
- Thank you.

908
01:09:12,022 --> 01:09:15,650
- Good news. This isn't a heart attack.
- I'm just hungry.

909
01:09:15,818 --> 01:09:20,697
They don't let visitors eat in the death
house. They must think we feed on air.

910
01:09:23,075 --> 01:09:25,785
Is that the machine
they use after an execution?

911
01:09:25,953 --> 01:09:29,956
Yes, ma'am. Just have to be
official about the whole thing.

912
01:09:30,749 --> 01:09:34,377
Thank God we're off the electric chair.
It's easier to take the needle.

913
01:09:34,545 --> 01:09:38,131
Just part of the job, you know. Let's
get you up and put some food in you.

914
01:09:38,299 --> 01:09:39,966
Who puts the needle in?

915
01:09:40,843 --> 01:09:42,427
That's private information.

916
01:09:42,595 --> 01:09:44,179
Is it you?

917
01:09:45,598 --> 01:09:49,767
We're not allowed to disclose any
specifics regardin' execution procedure.

918
01:09:51,520 --> 01:09:54,814
Sister, let me get you some food.
Then we'll send you home.

919
01:09:54,982 --> 01:09:57,942
- I gotta get back to Matt.
- I'm sorry, Sister.

920
01:09:58,110 --> 01:10:01,112
This is warden's orders.
You're through for the day.

921
01:10:04,783 --> 01:10:10,038
Where'd you go yesterday? You all right?
I asked what happened. Nobody'd tell me.

922
01:10:10,206 --> 01:10:12,916
You didn't know?
They told me they'd tell you...

923
01:10:13,083 --> 01:10:16,002
They took me into that little room.
They was measurin' me...

924
01:10:16,170 --> 01:10:18,588
- Measuring you?
- See how big a coffin I needed.

925
01:10:18,756 --> 01:10:21,674
Then I come back and you were gone.
I spent the day alone.

926
01:10:21,842 --> 01:10:24,135
Oh, Matt. I'm sorry.

927
01:10:26,305 --> 01:10:28,306
I'm so sorry.

928
01:10:33,062 --> 01:10:36,439
- You ever get lonely?
- Yeah, sure.

929
01:10:42,655 --> 01:10:46,741
Sometimes on Sundays when I smell
the neighborhood barbecues

930
01:10:46,909 --> 01:10:52,330
and I hear all the kids laughin'
and I'm sittin' in my room,

931
01:10:52,498 --> 01:10:54,165
I feel like a fool.

932
01:10:58,003 --> 01:11:02,173
What I miss most bein' here are women.

933
01:11:02,341 --> 01:11:06,928
You know, I used to sit at the bar,
just drinkin' and listenin' to music.

934
01:11:07,096 --> 01:11:09,681
I'd dance till
three or four in the morning.

935
01:11:09,848 --> 01:11:12,183
I ain't gonna lie.
I believe in doin' it.

936
01:11:12,351 --> 01:11:15,061
Me and my lady friends,
we'd grab a bottle, some weed...

937
01:11:15,229 --> 01:11:18,356
...go out in the woods and we'd do it.

938
01:11:18,524 --> 01:11:20,525
It's somethin' you miss, ma'am.

939
01:11:22,361 --> 01:11:23,528
Let's face it.

940
01:11:23,696 --> 01:11:26,864
If I had a husband and family, chances
are I'd be with them right now

941
01:11:27,032 --> 01:11:30,868
- instead of here visitin' with you.
- Yeah, true enough.

942
01:11:31,328 --> 01:11:32,787
I'm glad you're here.

943
01:11:38,377 --> 01:11:40,920
Do you want me to get a message
to your daughter?

944
01:11:47,553 --> 01:11:49,387
Let her be.

945
01:11:53,684 --> 01:11:55,476
Those things'll kill ya.

946
01:11:59,982 --> 01:12:02,066
I ain't gonna let 'em break me.

947
01:12:03,902 --> 01:12:06,571
I just pray God holds up my legs
on that last walk.

948
01:12:06,739 --> 01:12:09,407
It's the wait, it's the countdown
that gets to you.

949
01:12:12,036 --> 01:12:14,579
We're gonna know soon
about the federal appeal.

950
01:12:14,747 --> 01:12:18,291
And Hilton and I are meeting
with the governor this evening.

951
01:12:18,459 --> 01:12:21,711
Fat chance he's gonna do anything.
Risk his political butt for me?

952
01:12:21,879 --> 01:12:25,423
I wish I hadn't said all that shit
about Hitler and bein' a terrorist.

953
01:12:25,591 --> 01:12:27,467
Stupid!

954
01:12:29,595 --> 01:12:32,597
Hartman says there won't be
any more media interviews.

955
01:12:32,765 --> 01:12:36,768
Good. Keep my stupid mouth shut.

956
01:12:41,106 --> 01:12:44,442
I arranged for a lie detector test
for tomorrow morning.

957
01:12:44,610 --> 01:12:46,903
All right. There is some good news.

958
01:12:47,071 --> 01:12:50,448
The man that's giving
the test has serious doubts

959
01:12:50,616 --> 01:12:52,492
that they'll get an accurate result.

960
01:12:52,659 --> 01:12:55,411
- Why?
- Tomorrow's the day of your execution.

961
01:12:55,579 --> 01:12:59,457
You'll be under stress and the test
can mistake stress for dishonesty.

962
01:12:59,625 --> 01:13:01,751
No problem. I'm home free.

963
01:13:05,130 --> 01:13:06,881
You been readin' your Bible?

964
01:13:08,759 --> 01:13:10,968
I tried to last night.

965
01:13:12,054 --> 01:13:13,846
Makes me wanna sleep.

966
01:13:14,598 --> 01:13:16,182
I'm tryin' to stay conscious.

967
01:13:21,271 --> 01:13:24,107
I appreciate you tryin' to save me.

968
01:13:24,274 --> 01:13:27,777
Me and God, we got
our thing squared away.

969
01:13:27,945 --> 01:13:31,614
I know Jesus died on the cross for us,
and he's gonna take care of me

970
01:13:31,782 --> 01:13:34,033
when I appear before God
on Judgment Day.

971
01:13:36,537 --> 01:13:41,999
Redemption isn't a free admission ticket
you get because Jesus paid the price.

972
01:13:42,167 --> 01:13:47,505
You gotta participate in your own
redemption. You got some work to do.

973
01:13:48,173 --> 01:13:52,510
I think you should look at the Gospel of
John, chapter eight, where Jesus said,

974
01:13:53,679 --> 01:13:58,641
"You shall know the truth,
and the truth shall make you free."

975
01:14:00,894 --> 01:14:05,773
I'll check it out. I like that. "The
truth shall make you free." I like that.

976
01:14:06,775 --> 01:14:09,819
So I pass that lie detector test,
I'm home free.

977
01:14:11,196 --> 01:14:12,864
Matt...

978
01:14:14,741 --> 01:14:19,704
If you do die... as your friend,
I wanna help you die with dignity.

979
01:14:19,872 --> 01:14:22,498
You can't do that unless you own up...

980
01:14:22,666 --> 01:14:25,960
...to the part you played
in Walter and Hope's death.

981
01:14:44,771 --> 01:14:46,898
Hilton Barber, Bishop Norwich.

982
01:14:47,065 --> 01:14:49,484
Pleasure, Bishop. Here's the situation.

983
01:14:49,651 --> 01:14:53,905
Governor Benedict is a reluctant
supporter of capital punishment.

984
01:14:54,072 --> 01:14:57,366
He has the power to stop this execution
and save a man's life.

985
01:14:57,534 --> 01:15:00,244
It's the last vestige
of the divine right of kings.

986
01:15:00,412 --> 01:15:03,623
The trick is that we have to appeal
to him on a personal level,

987
01:15:03,790 --> 01:15:05,208
without any fanfare.

988
01:15:05,375 --> 01:15:07,418
That's why this is a private meeting.

989
01:15:07,586 --> 01:15:10,171
You must understand that,
in representing the State,

990
01:15:10,339 --> 01:15:15,927
I must carry out the laws and must
submerge my own personal views

991
01:15:16,094 --> 01:15:20,097
to carry out the will of the people.
I'll look carefully at this case.

992
01:15:20,265 --> 01:15:25,436
But unless there's some clear,
striking evidence for innocence,

993
01:15:25,604 --> 01:15:28,231
I will not interfere with the process.

994
01:15:31,026 --> 01:15:33,194
We still got the court, Sister.

995
01:15:33,362 --> 01:15:37,323
We might hit pay dirt
on one of the legal issues.

996
01:15:40,911 --> 01:15:45,289
Helen!
Helen, come to dinner!

997
01:15:47,125 --> 01:15:51,462
You're looking for a love
that's so big, it takes in all evil.

998
01:15:51,630 --> 01:15:56,008
Annunciations are common.
Incarnations are rare.

999
01:15:56,176 --> 01:15:58,219
You're not a saint, Helen.

1000
01:16:03,809 --> 01:16:06,477
Helen. Helen.

1001
01:16:06,895 --> 01:16:08,646
Helen.

1002
01:16:08,814 --> 01:16:11,399
- Helen.
- Oh, Mama.

1003
01:16:13,235 --> 01:16:17,530
- Are you OK?
- Oh, yes. I was just dreamin'.

1004
01:16:19,032 --> 01:16:22,618
- What time do you have to be there?
- Nine sharp.

1005
01:16:22,786 --> 01:16:26,247
- Did you set a clock?
- Yeah.

1006
01:16:27,874 --> 01:16:30,543
Oh... It's so bizarre.

1007
01:16:32,546 --> 01:16:35,840
A man's gonna be killed
in front of me tomorrow.

1008
01:16:37,718 --> 01:16:41,345
- Has he admitted anything?
- Oh, no.

1009
01:16:42,431 --> 01:16:47,184
He's so full of hate.
He doesn't trust anybody. He just...

1010
01:16:47,644 --> 01:16:49,895
He keeps pushin' me away.

1011
01:16:52,232 --> 01:16:54,275
You're in deep water, kid.

1012
01:16:56,236 --> 01:16:59,363
Do you remember
when you gave me a black eye?

1013
01:16:59,531 --> 01:17:04,201
- I had a fever.
- You were delirious, hysterical.

1014
01:17:05,370 --> 01:17:08,122
You were trying to get up
and run into the street.

1015
01:17:10,208 --> 01:17:13,711
You socked me in the eye
and you said you hated me.

1016
01:17:13,879 --> 01:17:16,964
You screamed, but I held you.
I held you tight.

1017
01:17:17,132 --> 01:17:22,345
Cos a mother's arms are strong
when her child's in danger.

1018
01:17:40,364 --> 01:17:43,282
I didn't sleep at all last night.

1019
01:17:43,450 --> 01:17:47,578
I didn't take that nerve medicine
they wanted to give me.

1020
01:17:48,664 --> 01:17:51,415
I'm lookin' death in the eyes.
I'm gettin' ready to go.

1021
01:17:56,963 --> 01:18:02,510
Listen, Matt, I want you to know
that I respect your need for privacy.

1022
01:18:03,387 --> 01:18:06,931
If you wanna be alone,
or be just with your family today,

1023
01:18:07,099 --> 01:18:08,766
I understand. I won't be offended.

1024
01:18:08,934 --> 01:18:11,102
You should be there, ma'am.

1025
01:18:11,269 --> 01:18:14,063
I'm gonna want somebody to talk to,
be there till the end.

1026
01:18:14,231 --> 01:18:15,898
I'll be there.

1027
01:18:18,777 --> 01:18:22,947
If only I knew I would die right away
with the first shot. Will I feel it?

1028
01:18:29,371 --> 01:18:31,163
The lungs go first.

1029
01:18:31,331 --> 01:18:35,626
Like a... fast choke.

1030
01:18:37,963 --> 01:18:39,797
That's gotta hurt.

1031
01:18:42,968 --> 01:18:48,139
They say that, uh...
the body doesn't move.

1032
01:18:49,975 --> 01:18:51,767
Doesn't shake.

1033
01:18:59,276 --> 01:19:01,360
My poor mama.

1034
01:19:07,242 --> 01:19:08,993
Any word from the Fifth Circuit?

1035
01:19:09,161 --> 01:19:11,328
None yet. That's a good sign.

1036
01:19:11,496 --> 01:19:15,791
They've had it a good while. Maybe that
means they see something substantive.

1037
01:19:15,959 --> 01:19:19,670
- I gotta go. I'll call you later.
- Thanks, Hilton.

1038
01:19:22,841 --> 01:19:24,884
Tell me somethin', Sister.

1039
01:19:25,051 --> 01:19:28,512
What is a nun doin'
in a place like this?

1040
01:19:28,680 --> 01:19:30,848
Shouldn't you be teachin' children?

1041
01:19:31,016 --> 01:19:33,517
Do you know what this man has done?

1042
01:19:33,685 --> 01:19:35,478
How he killed them kids?

1043
01:19:37,105 --> 01:19:39,857
What he did was evil.
I don't condone it.

1044
01:19:40,025 --> 01:19:43,110
I just don't see the sense in killing
people to say killing's wrong.

1045
01:19:43,278 --> 01:19:45,738
You know how the Bible says
an eye for an eye?

1046
01:19:45,906 --> 01:19:48,491
The Bible also asks
for death as a punishment

1047
01:19:48,658 --> 01:19:51,327
for adultery,
prostitution, homosexuality,

1048
01:19:51,495 --> 01:19:55,623
trespass upon sacred ground, profaning
the Sabbath and contempt of parents.

1049
01:19:55,791 --> 01:19:59,126
I ain't gonna get into no Bible quotin'
with no nun, cos I'm gonna lose.

1050
01:20:11,556 --> 01:20:13,724
She was only on the phone a few minutes

1051
01:20:13,892 --> 01:20:17,478
and she was fallin'
for the old Matt charm.

1052
01:20:18,563 --> 01:20:21,565
I had to take back that phone.
You were tryin' to steal my gal.

1053
01:20:21,733 --> 01:20:24,568
- You dog!
- She sounds like a great little gal.

1054
01:20:24,736 --> 01:20:26,737
She ain't so little, though.

1055
01:20:28,615 --> 01:20:31,283
You take care of her, Craig.
Don't do nothin' stupid.

1056
01:20:31,451 --> 01:20:35,663
She looks a bit like... What was
that girlfriend you had in high school?

1057
01:20:35,831 --> 01:20:37,915
I had lots of girls in high school.

1058
01:20:38,083 --> 01:20:40,918
- The one with the funny name.
- Funny name?

1059
01:20:41,086 --> 01:20:42,920
Maddie... Maldy. Maldy?

1060
01:20:44,589 --> 01:20:46,799
- Madrigal.
- Madrigal. Madrigal.

1061
01:20:46,967 --> 01:20:49,718
Madrigal Parmelee. Oh, she was hot!

1062
01:20:50,470 --> 01:20:53,430
- She was a nasty little thing!
- Matthew.

1063
01:20:53,598 --> 01:20:56,350
Sorry, Mama. She was a fine,
upstanding young woman.

1064
01:21:01,606 --> 01:21:04,817
How about you, Troy?
Got yourself a little girlfriend?

1065
01:21:04,985 --> 01:21:06,277
No.

1066
01:21:06,444 --> 01:21:08,487
- Why not?
- Ain't got time.

1067
01:21:08,655 --> 01:21:10,614
Too much fishin' and campin' to do.

1068
01:21:10,782 --> 01:21:13,784
- Troy just got a new tent.
- What kinda tent you got?

1069
01:21:13,952 --> 01:21:17,037
Army tent. Not like them
sissy ones with all them colors.

1070
01:21:17,205 --> 01:21:20,082
- Tell Matt about the other night.
- Campin' in the backyard.

1071
01:21:20,250 --> 01:21:23,669
I made him come in. I was worried.

1072
01:21:23,837 --> 01:21:26,171
I went out there
and I made him come in.

1073
01:21:26,339 --> 01:21:27,882
Mama, that ain't what happened.

1074
01:21:28,049 --> 01:21:30,885
- Go on. Tell him.
- Come on.

1075
01:21:33,096 --> 01:21:37,099
Me and my buddy Paul put up the tent,
cooked our own dinner.

1076
01:21:37,267 --> 01:21:41,896
We roasted potatoes in tinfoil on the
fire and cooked us some weenies.

1077
01:21:42,063 --> 01:21:44,148
Then what? Go on.

1078
01:21:45,650 --> 01:21:48,736
- About midnight...
- About nine o'clock, I think.

1079
01:21:48,904 --> 01:21:51,947
- We heard some kinda animal.
- What kinda animal?

1080
01:21:52,115 --> 01:21:53,240
It was big.

1081
01:21:53,408 --> 01:21:55,743
- Was it a bunny?
- A possum?

1082
01:21:55,911 --> 01:21:57,912
- Was it a squirrel?
- Was it a mouse?

1083
01:21:59,289 --> 01:22:03,292
- Shut up! It was big and nasty.
- Look me in the eye, little man.

1084
01:22:03,752 --> 01:22:06,629
Did you go in cos Mama told you to
or cos you were scared?

1085
01:22:06,796 --> 01:22:08,464
Now tell the truth.

1086
01:22:11,343 --> 01:22:13,802
Look me in the eye.

1087
01:22:16,598 --> 01:22:18,015
We got him!

1088
01:22:24,105 --> 01:22:26,190
Some people ask about your funeral.

1089
01:22:26,358 --> 01:22:29,276
I get real angry and say
"He's not dead yet."

1090
01:23:25,625 --> 01:23:29,211
- Sorry, folks. We have to wrap this up.
- It's early, isn't it?

1091
01:23:29,379 --> 01:23:31,422
Rules say they can stay till 6:45.

1092
01:23:34,259 --> 01:23:37,386
It's time for you folks
to be leavin' now.

1093
01:23:59,117 --> 01:24:01,452
- Here you go, Poncelet.
- Thanks, man.

1094
01:24:02,287 --> 01:24:04,204
I got my stuff in these pillowcases.

1095
01:24:04,372 --> 01:24:06,081
I'd like it if y'all
took it home with you.

1096
01:24:06,249 --> 01:24:10,252
I don't want the prison sendin' it.
Craig, you can divide up the stuff.

1097
01:24:10,420 --> 01:24:14,506
Except my boots from Marion. I want
to walk to my execution in these boots.

1098
01:24:15,425 --> 01:24:16,592
Up on your feet.

1099
01:24:17,135 --> 01:24:19,636
Y'all say your goodbyes now.

1100
01:24:38,114 --> 01:24:40,324
See you later, Matt.

1101
01:24:44,621 --> 01:24:47,456
- Bye.
- No goodbyes, little man.

1102
01:24:49,167 --> 01:24:51,001
- No, ma'am.
- Can't she hug him?

1103
01:24:52,337 --> 01:24:55,172
I'm sorry, Sister. Security reasons.

1104
01:25:03,348 --> 01:25:06,600
Don't cry, Mama.
I don't wanna see no cryin'.

1105
01:25:06,768 --> 01:25:09,103
I'm not sayin' goodbye now.

1106
01:25:09,896 --> 01:25:13,065
- I'll call you tonight.
- See you, Matt. Stay strong.

1107
01:25:14,567 --> 01:25:16,401
Don't cry, Mama. I'll call you later.

1108
01:25:17,862 --> 01:25:19,738
We love you, Mattie.

1109
01:25:27,914 --> 01:25:32,918
If I'd put my arms around my boy,
I'd never have let go.

1110
01:25:45,181 --> 01:25:46,890
Is my mama all right?!

1111
01:25:49,060 --> 01:25:49,935
She's fine, Matt.

1112
01:25:52,063 --> 01:25:53,897
All right. Goodbye.

1113
01:26:00,572 --> 01:26:04,908
I never had shrimp before.
They're pretty good.

1114
01:26:08,121 --> 01:26:12,082
So what did he say? What's the word
on the lie detector test?

1115
01:26:13,960 --> 01:26:16,837
Your answers showed stress,
as predicted

1116
01:26:17,005 --> 01:26:19,339
and the results were inconclusive.

1117
01:26:19,507 --> 01:26:25,012
Man... Was the dude sure?
Absolutely, positively sure?

1118
01:26:27,807 --> 01:26:31,768
I felt all right answerin' them
questions. I didn't feel no stress.

1119
01:26:33,146 --> 01:26:34,730
I can't believe I failed it.

1120
01:26:34,898 --> 01:26:38,275
You'd have to be a robot or insane
not to feel stress now.

1121
01:26:38,443 --> 01:26:40,903
I can't believe that test
didn't come out right.

1122
01:26:45,074 --> 01:26:49,286
Let's talk about what happened.
Let's talk about that night.

1123
01:26:49,454 --> 01:26:51,747
I don't wanna talk about that.

1124
01:27:23,613 --> 01:27:25,322
- Get outta the car.
- Hey, you're a pretty bunny.

1125
01:27:25,490 --> 01:27:28,659
You're trespassing.
This is private property.

1126
01:27:28,826 --> 01:27:30,160
Let's go.

1127
01:27:30,328 --> 01:27:32,162
You're under arrest.
Step outta the car.

1128
01:27:32,330 --> 01:27:34,331
We'll just leave. We didn't know...

1129
01:27:34,499 --> 01:27:36,458
Get outta the car!

1130
01:27:36,834 --> 01:27:39,795
- Where are we going?
- There's a little bar back here.

1131
01:27:39,963 --> 01:27:43,090
- Our boss is in the bar.
- We can't let you go. You been bad.

1132
01:27:43,258 --> 01:27:46,051
- Our boss is gonna be pissed.
- Maybe he'll let you go.

1133
01:27:47,053 --> 01:27:51,014
Well, here we are. This is the bar.

1134
01:27:51,182 --> 01:27:53,350
- Can we get you a drink?
- Kneel down.

1135
01:27:54,185 --> 01:27:55,435
I'm pissed off!

1136
01:27:55,603 --> 01:28:00,315
Pissed off at them kids. Pissed off
at their parents comin' to see me die.

1137
01:28:00,483 --> 01:28:02,693
Pissed off at myself
for lettin' Vitello do it.

1138
01:28:02,860 --> 01:28:06,196
I got my last words. I know what to say
to the Percys and the Delacroixs.

1139
01:28:06,364 --> 01:28:08,532
Your last words
will be words of hatred?

1140
01:28:08,700 --> 01:28:11,159
Clyde Percy wants
to inject me hisself!

1141
01:28:11,327 --> 01:28:13,870
Think of how angry he must be.

1142
01:28:14,038 --> 01:28:16,540
He's never gonna see his daughter again.

1143
01:28:16,708 --> 01:28:19,876
Never hold her, love her,
laugh with her.

1144
01:28:20,044 --> 01:28:25,007
You've robbed these parents of so much.
They have nothin' but sorrow. No joy.

1145
01:28:25,174 --> 01:28:26,758
That is what you have given them.

1146
01:28:31,472 --> 01:28:35,392
- What possessed you to be in the woods?
- I told ya. I was stoned outta my head.

1147
01:28:35,560 --> 01:28:40,397
You were harassing couples for weeks
before this happened. Months!

1148
01:28:42,233 --> 01:28:45,152
- What was it?
- What do you mean?

1149
01:28:45,320 --> 01:28:48,655
Did you look up to Vitello?
Did you think he was cool?

